text: Bolshoy Kuganak () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kuganaksky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 2,368 as of 2010. There are 24 streets. == Geography == It is located 25 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Bolshoy Kuganak
